# OpenClaw VM — COMPOSE-LEVEL env only. Copy to .env and fill in.
# The real .env is gitignored and written by the Ubuntu autoinstall at provision time
# (it sets ONLY PANEL_PASSWORD here; PANEL_DOMAIN is left blank to auto-derive).
# NEVER commit a real .env.
#
# IMPORTANT — two separate .env files, do NOT conflate them:
#   * THIS file (/opt/openclaw-vm/.env) is the COMPOSE-LEVEL env. docker compose reads
#     it for ${VAR} substitution into the panel + caddy services. It holds NO
#     provider/messaging secrets and is NOT the agent's env.
#   * The AGENT'S secrets live in the SHARED data dir (./data/.env -> ~/.openclaw/.env)
#     and are WRITTEN BY THE PANEL, not here. OpenClaw resolves ${VAR} in
#     openclaw.json from ./data/.env at gateway start; the host applier restarts it.
#     firstboot.sh auto-generates OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN into ./data/.env.

# === CloudHosting setup panel + TLS (compose-level substitution) ===
# Panel login password. REQUIRED — the panel fails closed (PANEL_REQUIRE_AUTH=1) if
# empty. Strong unique value per VM. This is the ONLY secret the autoinstall sets.
PANEL_PASSWORD=REPLACE_ME
# Public host the panel is served on (TLS via Let's Encrypt, :8443). Leave BLANK to
# have firstboot.sh derive it from the primary IPv4 as
# vps-<3rd octet>-<4th octet>.cloudhosting.lv (A-record exists by convention).
PANEL_DOMAIN=

# === Optional turnkey avots ===
# If set, the panel auto-connects avots as the primary on first start (the client
# does nothing). Leave blank to have the client paste their key in the panel.
# AVOTS_API_KEY=av_mcp_...

# === File ownership ===
# The agent + panel both run as uid 1000 (the image's node user; hardcoded in
# docker-compose.yml). firstboot.sh chowns ./data to 1000 so the panel's 0600
# openclaw.json/.env stay agent-readable. Override with OPENCLAW_UID/OPENCLAW_GID only
# if a future image changes its uid.

# === Misc ===
# OPENCLAW_TZ=Europe/Riga
# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789   # host loopback port; container port is fixed at 18789

# ===========================================================================
# PROVIDER + MESSAGING SECRETS ARE *NOT* SET HERE.
# ===========================================================================
# Set them in the panel (admin UI), NOT here. The panel writes them into
# ./data/openclaw.json + ./data/.env and restarts the agent via the host applier:
#   * provider + API key   -> openclaw.json models.providers.<id> (apiKey: ${VAR})
#                             + ./data/.env (AVOTS_API_KEY / OPENAI_API_KEY / ...)
#   * messaging bot token  -> ./data/.env (TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN / DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN)
#   * owner id (allowFrom) -> openclaw.json channels.<type>.allowFrom (the owner-lock)
# Open https://<PANEL_DOMAIN>:8443 after first boot, log in with PANEL_PASSWORD.
